DATAGLOW uses the following third-party libraries, each under its own license.

Redistributed (vendored) in this repository under assets/duckdb/. Each
library's own license text is included alongside its files:

- DuckDB-WASM — MIT License — https://github.com/duckdb/duckdb-wasm
  (see assets/duckdb/DUCKDB-WASM-LICENSE)
- Apache Arrow (apache-arrow) — Apache License 2.0 — https://github.com/apache/arrow
  (see assets/duckdb/vendor/apache-arrow/LICENSE.txt)
- tslib — 0BSD License — https://github.com/microsoft/tslib
  (see assets/duckdb/vendor/tslib/LICENSE.txt)
- FlatBuffers (flatbuffers) — Apache License 2.0 — https://github.com/google/flatbuffers
  (see assets/duckdb/vendor/flatbuffers/LICENSE)

Loaded at runtime via CDN (not redistributed in this repository):

- Plotly.js — MIT License — https://github.com/plotly/plotly.js
- SheetJS (xlsx) — Apache License 2.0 — https://github.com/SheetJS/sheetjs
- Pyodide — Mozilla Public License 2.0 — https://github.com/pyodide/pyodide
- WebR — MIT (WebR itself) / GPL (bundled R runtime) — https://github.com/r-wasm/webr

DATAGLOW's own statistical and machine-learning features are original
implementations of publicly published academic methods. No novelty is
claimed over this prior art. See the in-app "About & Attributions" panel
(Settings tab) for the full list of cited sources.
